            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_001844_0001" n="0001"/><!-- Change both @facs and @n -->
	<!-- Start each page with a <pb> formatted as above -->
<!-- If this is a letter or similar with an opener (with content such as dateline and/or salute) add it. For example: -->
<opener>
<lb/><add place="margintop" rend="gray" hand="#U"><space extent="1" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>LX</add> 
<lb/><dateline><space extent="3" unit="words"/><placeName><settlement type="town"><choice><orig>Quillimane</orig><reg>Quelimane</reg></choice></settlement></placeName> <date when="1862-10-17">17<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> <choice><abbr>Oct.</abbr><expan>October</expan></choice>      
<lb/><space extent="6" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>1862</date></dateline> 
<lb/>
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/><salute>Dear Sir</salute><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->
</opener>
<lb/><p><space extent="8" unit="chars"/>We were obliged to      
<lb/>come into this river to cut wood
<lb/>a few days ago &amp; when on our
<lb/>way down met a boat from <unclear cert="low">to</unclear>
<lb/><choice><abbr>M.S.</abbr><expan>Motor Ship</expan></choice> Rapid with your letter
<lb/>and lots of provisions for the
<lb/><placeName><settlement type="town">Oxford</settlement></placeName> &amp; <placeName><settlement type="town">Cambridge</settlement></placeName> mission 
<lb/>As we are full of provisions
<lb/>we cannot possibly take them
<lb/>on board our deck even being lumbered
<lb/>up with draught <term type="animal_foodstuff">oxen</term>. I came
<lb/>up with the man of war's boat</p>

<!-- The following segment continues on from the end of the page. AW -->
<cb rend="vertical left"/><ab>
<lb/>which led me to fill <unclear cert="low">a</unclear> sheet of foolscap <!-- I cannot make out this word. JM --><!-- Fixed. AW --> &amp; I am not <!-- I cannot make out this word. JM --> 
<lb/><unclear cert="medium">through</unclear> so it is his own fault. The necessary consequence 
<lb/>in fact of his letter I cannot finish mine
<lb/><space extent="8" unit="words"/><persName>David Livingstone</persName></ab>  <!-- Oxygen would not allow me to mark this line as a closer or as a signature. JM --><!-- We may need to get guidance on this. AW -->
                
    <pb facs="liv_001844_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">and have arranged with <persName>Colonel
<lb/>Nunés</persName> to send down his launch
<lb/>to take the mission provisions
<lb/>I must say he behaves very
<lb/>handsomely in the matter for
<lb/>everyone else refuses to lend
<lb/>either launch or boat but by
<lb/>promising to tow this one out
<lb/>and in again over the bar he has
<lb/>kindly assented to my request
<lb/>He is a good fellow and his
<lb/>nephew <persName>José Mellitás Nunes</persName> 
<lb/>is no less. <persName>Waller</persName> was down
<lb/>here lately (<date when="1862-10-05">5<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi>October</date> and took
<lb/>what provisions &amp; <term type="foodstuff">grog</term> he could

    <pb facs="liv_001844_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>get. I am glad to see plenty
<lb/>of medical comforts. <subst><del><unclear cert="low">very</unclear></del><add place="over-text">They</add></subst> will
<lb/>be very acceptable. I believe
<lb/>they all felt better for the <term type="foodstuff">brandy</term>
<lb/>we took up part of the way
<lb/>and this fresh supply will
<lb/>no doubt be useful too -
<lb/>should their reverences ever
<lb/>get "drunk and disorderly" <unclear cert="medium">thereon</unclear>
<lb/>may hence the capital excuse
<lb/>that it was the "necessary
<lb/>consequence" of my having
<lb/>towed it over the bar. In my
<lb/>simplicity I have invariably

    <pb facs="liv_001844_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>ascribed my mistakes to my
<lb/>own stupidity or worse &amp; imagined
<lb/>it would have been <hi rend="underline">unmanly</hi>
<lb/>to blame another for what I had
<lb/>deliberately done - but the longer one
<lb/><unclear cert="high">lives</unclear> the more one learns (sage
<lb/>observation)and our friends up
<lb/><placeName><geogName type="river">Shire</geogName></placeName> are our friends still and
<lb/>I hope will be to the end of the 
<lb/>chapter. <space extent="3" unit="chars"/> Thanks for your
<lb/>kind letter, and be good enough
<lb/>to communicate the little <w>inform<supplied>-</supplied>
<lb break="no"/>-ation</w> I have at present to give
<lb/>to the bishop. I rejoice that a 
<lb/>new bishop will come. Mistakes
<lb/>and disappointments will happen.
<lb/>but the end of all these Christian
<lb/>efforts will be glorious. Please
<lb/>present kind salutations to your
<lb/>Lady &amp; say to <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Frere</persName> that I shall write
<lb/>him as soon as possible. He put <add place="below">^</add> <add place="above">me</add> on a tack</p>

